Header exchange with RabbitMQ 
    We will create a headers exchange named demo.headers.ex with two queues:

1. PDF Queue (demo.q.pdf) – receives messages where format=pdf AND type=report (x-match=all)
2. Priority Queue (demo.q.priority) – receives messages where priority=high OR department=finance (x-match=any)

Important: x-match is part of the binding arguments (exchange→queue binding)

1. Create Springboot-RabbitMQ-HeaderExchange with web, spring for rabbitmq dependency

2. Configure RabbitMQ properties

3. Define Headers Exchange + Queues + Bindings 
             RabbitMQ supports a Headers exchange type.  In a headers exchange binding, you specify x-match and header criteria. x-match=all means AND; x-match=any means OR. 
Also: x-match belongs on the binding, not on the message. 

@Configuration
public class RabbitTopologyConfig {

    public static final String HEADERS_EXCHANGE = "demo.headers.ex";

    public static final String Q_PDF = "demo.q.pdf";
    public static final String Q_PRIORITY = "demo.q.priority";

    @Bean
    public HeadersExchange headersExchange() {
        // durable=true, autoDelete=false
        return new HeadersExchange(HEADERS_EXCHANGE, true, false);
    }

    @Bean
    public Queue pdfQueue() {
        return new Queue(Q_PDF, true);
    }

    @Bean
    public Queue priorityQueue() {
        return new Queue(Q_PRIORITY, true);
    }

    @Bean
    public Binding pdfBinding() {
        // x-match=all => ALL headers must match
        // format=pdf AND type=report
        Map<String, Object> args = Map.of(
                "x-match", "all",
                "format", "pdf",
                "type", "report"
        );

        // For headers exchange, routingKey is ignored; keep it empty string.
        return new Binding(Q_PDF, DestinationType.QUEUE, HEADERS_EXCHANGE, "", args);
    }

    @Bean
    public Binding priorityBinding() {
        // x-match=any => ANY header match is enough
        // priority=high OR department=finance
        Map<String, Object> args = Map.of(
                "x-match", "any",
                "priority", "high",
                "department", "finance"
        );

        return new Binding(Q_PRIORITY, DestinationType.QUEUE, HEADERS_EXCHANGE, "", args);
    }
}



