Reliability & Fault Tolerance module for Spring Boot + Messaging 

A. Message Durability
What problem it solves
   - What happens to messages if RabbitMQ crashes or restarts?

Without durability
1. Messages live only in memory
2. Broker restart ⇒ messages lost

With durability
1. Messages written to disk
2. Survive broker restarts

How durability works (3 things must align)
✅ Durable Exchange
          new DirectExchange("order.exchange", true, false);

✅ Durable Queue
  QueueBuilder.durable("order.queue").build(); 

✅ Persistent Message
rabbitTemplate.convertAndSend(
    "order.exchange",
    "order.created",
    payload,
    msg -> {
        msg.getMessageProperties()
           .setDeliveryMode(MessageDeliveryMode.PERSISTENT);
        return msg;
    }
);

Durable exchange + durable queue + persistent message = durability

Real‑world example
✅ Order creation
✅ Payment events
✅ Financial transactions

B. Publisher Confirms
What problem it solves
    How do I know RabbitMQ actually received my message?

Without confirms:
1. You publish
2. Network glitch happens
3. You think message is sent
4. Broker never got it ❌

How Publisher Confirms work
1. RabbitMQ sends an ACK / NACK back to the producer.

Spring Boot example
