C. Consumer Acknowledgements
What problem it solves
    When should RabbitMQ remove a message from the queue?”

Three acknowledgement modes
1. AUTO(default) -  Message delivered → immediately ACKed

2. MANUAL (recommended)
✅ Full control
✅ Required for retries, DLQ, idempotency

@RabbitListener(queues = "order.queue")
public void onMessage(OrderEvent event,
                      Message message,
                      Channel channel) throws Exception {

    try {
        process(event);
        channel.basicAck(message.getMessageProperties().getDeliveryTag(), false);
    } catch (Exception e) {
        channel.basicNack(
            message.getMessageProperties().getDeliveryTag(),
            false,
            false // requeue?
        );
    }
}

